Case Study: Incident Dashboard Analysis (Ticket Volume + Excel)

Issue:
High number of incidents were raised daily, impacting SLA and increasing resolution time.

Monitoring Approach:
Used ServiceNow dashboard to track:

Total ticket volume per day

Priority distribution (P1, P2, P3)

Incident trends over time

Exported the incident data into Excel for deeper analysis.

Excel Dataset:
Sample dataset uploaded as: incident_dashboard_sample.xlsx

Columns Used:

Incident_ID

Created_At

Priority

Category

Status

Assigned_To

Excel Analysis:

Created Pivot Tables to analyze:

Tickets per day

Tickets by priority

Tickets by category

Identified peak hours using time-based grouping

Used bar and line charts to visualize trends

Insights:

Peak ticket volume observed during evening hours

Majority of incidents were P2 category

Login and Order issues were most frequent

Repeated incidents indicated missing permanent fixes

Root Cause:
High system usage during peak hours and recurring defects in specific modules.

Resolution:

Fixed recurring issues with development team

Increased support team availability during peak hours

Improved monitoring and alerting

Outcome:

Reduced ticket volume by ~30%

Improved SLA compliance

Faster resolution time

Tools Used:
ServiceNow | Excel (Pivot Tables, Charts)
